---
title: Cozy Chickpea and Egg Skillet with Shakshuka Spices and Feta Cheese
description: This tomato-y chickpea and egg bake, which is inspired by North African shakshuka, is one of those versatile dishes that feels like a meal of champions. The ingredients are simmered until they’re sultry, stewy, and saucy, then the eggs are plopped in and cooked using the warmth and steam from the whole mixture. On the side, you’ve got toasty baguette slices, which are perfect for scooping up all that amazingness with your hands.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/cozy-chickpea-and-egg-skillet-3f3b8f00.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/cozy-chickpea-and-egg-skillet-001be869.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 660 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 78 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 19 g
  sodium: 1170 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cozy-chickpea-and-egg-skillet-59669c1499052d2b382f1682
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: African
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat (use an ovenproof pan if you have one). Add onion and garlic. Cook, tossing, until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in @shakshuka spice blend{1%tbsp} and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add chickpeas and @crushed tomatoes{1%400g can}. Stir to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir @water{1%cup} into pan. Bring to a simmer and let bubble until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir in half the parsley and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp} (to taste). Season with salt and pepper.

Make two small wells in tomato mixture. Carefully crack an @eggs{2} into each. Sprinkle salt, pepper, and @feta cheese{1/2%unit} over everything. Transfer to oven and bake until eggs reach desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, continue cooking on stove, covered, until eggs reach desired doneness, 5-7 minutes.

Meanwhile, cut @demi-baguette{1} into slices and place on a #baking sheet{}. Sprinkle with a drizzle of olive oil, then season with salt and pepper. Toast in oven until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Sprinkle remaining parsley over pan, along with any remaining chili flakes (to taste). Divide between #bowls{} and serve with toasts for dipping.